  "body": "I noticed that there are variables defined as `crosslink_committee` that have different types:\r\n\r\n### As a `List[ValidatorIndex]`\r\n\r\n- Inside [`get_attestation_participants(...)`](https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/blob/dev/specs/core/0_beacon-chain.md#get_attestation_participants)\r\n- [Per-block processing/attestations](https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/blob/dev/specs/core/0_beacon-chain.md#attestations-1):  \"Verify bitfields and aggregate signature...\"\r\n\r\n### As a `Tuple[List[ValidatorIndex], ShardNumber]`\r\n\r\n- `get_crosslink_committees_at_slot(...)` returns `List[Tuple[List[ValidatorIndex], ShardNumber]]`, inferring that a `crosslink_committee` is `Tuple[List[ValidatorIndex], ShardNumber]`.\r\n\r\nThere are some other instances around the place, but I think you get the point.\r\n\r\nNot a huge deal but I found it to be a bit confusing especially when trying to figure out the `winning_root` function.",
