    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "The \"full\" type of a crosslink committee is arguably `Tuple[List[ValidatorIndex], ShardNumber, SlotNumber]`. In most cases the slot number is known from context—hence `Tuple[List[ValidatorIndex], ShardNumber]`—and in some cases the shard number is also known from context—hence `List[ValidatorIndex]`.\r\n\r\nDoes that make sense? I think using the simplest \"reduced\" type based in context is fine, and using `Tuple[List[ValidatorIndex], ShardNumber]` or `Tuple[List[ValidatorIndex], ShardNumber, SlotNumber]` everywhere would be overkill.\r\n\r\nFeel free to reopen :)",
